271
00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:42.940
Druwesh.

272
00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:55.300
Good afternoon, everyone. First, I would like to thank the

273
00:15:55.360 --> 00:15:58.930
organizer for giving me the opportunity to present my

274
00:15:58.960 --> 00:15:59.420
work.

275
00:16:08.520 --> 00:16:10.140
I don't have any disclosures.

276
00:16:11.720 --> 00:16:15.260
So adenomatous colorectal polyposis is a

277
00:16:15.540 --> 00:16:19.420
rare condition. It is characterized by the presence

278
00:16:19.460 --> 00:16:23.240
of several polyps distributed throughout the colon and the

279
00:16:23.300 --> 00:16:23.699
rectum.

280
00:16:24.540 --> 00:16:26.980
The number of these polyps in the colon

281
00:16:28.700 --> 00:16:32.520
determines the type of polyposis that range from

282
00:16:32.580 --> 00:16:36.200
attenuated to profuse forms. Even though the

283
00:16:36.260 --> 00:16:39.660
polyps are benign lesions, they may evolve into

284
00:16:39.740 --> 00:16:41.520
colorectal adenocarcinoma.

285
00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:46.940
The adenoma adenocarcinoma sequence is well-known,

286
00:16:47.140 --> 00:16:51.040
well-established. First, alterations in APC or

287
00:16:51.100 --> 00:16:53.380
cadherin beta genes are

288
00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:58.200
altered and leads to an uncontrolled

289
00:16:58.260 --> 00:17:02.110
proliferation. Then MAPK pathway and

290
00:17:02.160 --> 00:17:05.840
TGF beta pathways are involved, and they

291
00:17:06.020 --> 00:17:09.720
go further with promoting tumor growth,

292
00:17:10.320 --> 00:17:14.181
and they promote adenoma polyp progression.

293
00:17:14.740 --> 00:17:18.381
Then there are the loss of p53 and other

294
00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:23.421
alteration that drive the transition from

295
00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:27.100
high-grade dysplasia to an invasive carcinoma.

296
00:17:28.600 --> 00:17:30.400
These processes are mainly

297
00:17:31.220 --> 00:17:34.780
affected in sporadic cancer. However, some

298
00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:38.700
hereditary colorectal syndromes can also be affected.

299
00:17:39.020 --> 00:17:42.980
In fact, they are in about 10 to 12% of the cases.

300
00:17:43.860 --> 00:17:47.780
And we were, in this work, more interested in the syndromes

301
00:17:47.820 --> 00:17:51.100
that are associated with adenomatous polyposis, the red ones.

302
00:17:52.700 --> 00:17:55.980
Despite the fact that we have

303
00:17:56.480 --> 00:18:00.240
greatly advanced in the sequencing techniques and

304
00:18:00.300 --> 00:18:03.980
improved the genetic counseling,

305
00:18:04.360 --> 00:18:08.292
there are still a large proportion of peopleThat remain

306
00:18:08.352 --> 00:18:11.912
genetically unexplained even though they have quite

307
00:18:11.952 --> 00:18:12.572
suggestive

308
00:18:13.432 --> 00:18:14.992
phenotype of polyposis.

309
00:18:16.612 --> 00:18:18.812
There might be several reasons for that.

310
00:18:19.492 --> 00:18:23.412
First, the germline pathogenic variant could be in the

311
00:18:23.452 --> 00:18:27.292
known gene, but undetectable with current

312
00:18:27.332 --> 00:18:28.092
technologies.

313
00:18:29.092 --> 00:18:32.932
Another explanation could be that the germline variant could

314
00:18:33.032 --> 00:18:36.132
affect other genes that have not been identified yet.

315
00:18:37.052 --> 00:18:40.752
The polyposis could also be driven by

316
00:18:40.812 --> 00:18:44.612
epigenetic modifications or multigenic factors.

317
00:18:45.192 --> 00:18:46.192
Other explanation

318
00:18:47.352 --> 00:18:51.172
might be because of mosaicism or

319
00:18:51.232 --> 00:18:55.152
also the involvement of environmental factors that

320
00:18:55.192 --> 00:18:55.912
have not been

321
00:18:56.852 --> 00:19:00.152
very described yet. And in this work, we were

322
00:19:00.332 --> 00:19:03.171
mostly interested in these two last points.

323
00:19:04.932 --> 00:19:07.092
First, the somatic mosaicism.

324
00:19:08.392 --> 00:19:12.071
It appears when a mutation occurs during embryonic

325
00:19:12.252 --> 00:19:12.952
development.

326
00:19:14.552 --> 00:19:18.392
The earlier the mutation occur, the

327
00:19:18.452 --> 00:19:20.392
more widely is

328
00:19:21.812 --> 00:19:24.752
distributed the mutation throughout the

329
00:19:25.572 --> 00:19:26.072
patient's

330
00:19:28.372 --> 00:19:31.452
body. And if the mutation appear

331
00:19:31.912 --> 00:19:35.892
around two weeks after fertilization, then it can be absent from the

332
00:19:35.972 --> 00:19:39.272
germ cells and not inherited from the parents.

333
00:19:39.792 --> 00:19:43.392
If the mutation occur around or after the

334
00:19:43.492 --> 00:19:47.142
third week after fertilization, they can

335
00:19:47.532 --> 00:19:51.272
be absent from the blood, even if it's present in the colon.

336
00:19:53.612 --> 00:19:54.932
The other major point

337
00:19:55.872 --> 00:19:59.652
that we will discuss is the genotoxic microbiota

338
00:20:00.012 --> 00:20:01.432
that can affect

339
00:20:02.332 --> 00:20:05.472
colonic lesions. It has been shown that colonic

340
00:20:05.512 --> 00:20:09.352
microbiota may contain bacteria producing the colibactin.

341
00:20:09.772 --> 00:20:12.092
The colibactin is a genotoxic product

342
00:20:13.492 --> 00:20:16.172
produced by some bacteria, and that

343
00:20:16.311 --> 00:20:20.192
induce some

344
00:20:20.712 --> 00:20:24.592
specific DNA damage that are well known as the

345
00:20:24.712 --> 00:20:28.092
ones giving rise to these two cosmic molecular

346
00:20:28.192 --> 00:20:31.412
signature. These signatures have been

347
00:20:31.452 --> 00:20:34.892
described in normal mucosa, adenoma, and

348
00:20:34.912 --> 00:20:38.392
carcinoma, especially highly prevalent in

349
00:20:38.532 --> 00:20:42.272
colorectal carcinoma. And it is also known

350
00:20:42.332 --> 00:20:45.852
that some of APC mutation have been

351
00:20:45.972 --> 00:20:49.272
specifically associated with the colibactin

352
00:20:49.392 --> 00:20:50.092
exposure.

353
00:20:53.172 --> 00:20:56.592
So what we did in our study is that we

354
00:20:56.652 --> 00:21:00.432
enrolled a series of 125 patients

355
00:21:00.812 --> 00:21:03.772
with unexplained colorectal adenomatous polyposis.

356
00:21:04.252 --> 00:21:07.352
All these patients were negative for germline

357
00:21:07.362 --> 00:21:11.272
sequencing, and they didn't have any family

358
00:21:11.312 --> 00:21:11.742
history.

359
00:21:12.632 --> 00:21:16.582
From this series, we discarded 10 patients because of low DNA

360
00:21:16.582 --> 00:21:17.012
quality.

361
00:21:18.812 --> 00:21:22.112
And then for the remaining patients, we

362
00:21:23.072 --> 00:21:26.972
were able to collect from one to nine different

363
00:21:27.132 --> 00:21:30.992
samples, mainly neoplastic samples, but also some

364
00:21:31.512 --> 00:21:33.452
normal colonic mucosa samples.

365
00:21:34.732 --> 00:21:38.152
We assume that APC mosaicism could be

366
00:21:38.272 --> 00:21:40.032
assessed if one

367
00:21:40.892 --> 00:21:44.692
PV of APC could be detected and

368
00:21:44.772 --> 00:21:48.392
shared between three independent neoplastic lesions,

369
00:21:48.912 --> 00:21:52.492
or one neoplastic lesion and one normal mucosa.

370
00:21:53.112 --> 00:21:55.892
Unfortunately, in this series, 55

371
00:21:55.932 --> 00:21:59.712
patients were not

372
00:21:59.752 --> 00:22:03.672
analyzed for APC mosaicism because we were not able to

373
00:22:04.412 --> 00:22:07.952
get enough sufficient number of lesions to

374
00:22:07.992 --> 00:22:09.352
assess this status.

375
00:22:10.492 --> 00:22:11.012
However,

376
00:22:12.012 --> 00:22:15.452
for the 60 remaining patients, we were able to

377
00:22:15.492 --> 00:22:19.392
describe a mosaicism of APC in one-third

378
00:22:19.552 --> 00:22:21.652
of the cases that were tested.

379
00:22:25.072 --> 00:22:29.012
More generally, we found a pathogenic variant of

380
00:22:29.052 --> 00:22:32.852
APC in 94% of the lesions. The

381
00:22:32.912 --> 00:22:36.612
one that were wild type for APC were driven by

382
00:22:36.692 --> 00:22:39.992
other oncogenes like KRAS, BRAF or beta-catenin.

383
00:22:40.612 --> 00:22:42.672
And the more frequently altered

384
00:22:43.852 --> 00:22:47.312
pathways in this series were like in other polyps,

385
00:22:48.372 --> 00:22:50.392
RAS, WNT, and TP53

386
00:22:51.232 --> 00:22:51.752
pathways.

387
00:22:54.112 --> 00:22:57.872
Importantly, among the patients that we found with a

388
00:22:57.892 --> 00:23:01.652
shared mosaic APC variant, we found

389
00:23:01.712 --> 00:23:02.432
these variants,

390
00:23:03.352 --> 00:23:07.172
retrospectively, in the blood sample for two patients.

391
00:23:07.252 --> 00:23:11.212
This mutation was detected at a very low frequency.

392
00:23:12.572 --> 00:23:13.672
In one of these case,

393
00:23:14.672 --> 00:23:17.732
we observed a transmission of the mosaic

394
00:23:20.052 --> 00:23:23.672
mutation, and the woman that was

395
00:23:23.732 --> 00:23:27.432
