436
00:26:02.676 --> 00:26:05.376
Finally, when we looked more carefully at the clonal

437
00:26:05.396 --> 00:26:07.256
architecture of the

438
00:26:08.076 --> 00:26:10.376
polyposis, we found that the

439
00:26:10.856 --> 00:26:14.796
colibactin-associated APC variants were subclonal

440
00:26:14.856 --> 00:26:18.715
in the mosaic patients and fully clonal in the non-mosaic

441
00:26:18.796 --> 00:26:22.136
patients. And we can see here two examples

442
00:26:22.416 --> 00:26:25.965
showing that the blue here, APC with

443
00:26:25.976 --> 00:26:29.576
the colibactin motif, were subclonal in this case and fully

444
00:26:29.616 --> 00:26:30.596
clonal in here.

445
00:26:33.196 --> 00:26:37.076
To conclude, what we show is that APC mosaicism may account for

446
00:26:37.116 --> 00:26:40.776
one-third of unexplained cases of colorectal adenomatous

447
00:26:40.836 --> 00:26:41.516
polyposis.

448
00:26:42.396 --> 00:26:46.336
This suggests that mosaicism should be systematically considered

449
00:26:46.716 --> 00:26:50.596
in these cases, even though the diagnostic strategy

450
00:26:50.616 --> 00:26:52.276
is demanding and time-consuming.

451
00:26:52.896 --> 00:26:56.736
Moreover, the infection of colibactin-producing bacteria is

452
00:26:56.796 --> 00:26:59.736
highly prevalent and may act as a co-factor

453
00:27:00.116 --> 00:27:03.886
mimicking the phenotype of polyposis and representing

454
00:27:04.536 --> 00:27:06.476
