751
00:44:09.006 --> 00:44:09.216
Thanks.

752
00:44:11.716 --> 00:44:15.216
Great presentation. Just a quick question about single

753
00:44:15.276 --> 00:44:18.396
nucleotide polymorphisms in the genes of interest.

754
00:44:18.936 --> 00:44:22.886
Are there any stratifying SNPs that allow you to separate these

755
00:44:22.916 --> 00:44:23.806
populations-

756
00:44:24.056 --> 00:44:24.526
Oh, yeah

757
00:44:25.316 --> 00:44:29.016
... that can predict the collagen as well as the immune infiltration?

758
00:44:29.596 --> 00:44:33.356
Yeah. So we did whole exome sequencing to

